In large skillet, brown ground turkey until thoroughly cooked; drain. In same skillet, combine water, margarine or butter, rice mix, seasonings and turkey. Bring to a boil; reduce heat to low. Cover; simmer 20 minutes. Stir in soup, mushrooms, celery and bell pepper; return to a simmer. Cover; simmer 5 to 10 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender. Let stand 3 minutes. Stir before serving.